Reasoning: The paper introduces a new calculus, the safe lambda calculus, which is a syntactic condition of higher-order grammars that constrains the occurrences of variables in the production rules according to their type-theoretic order. This topic is closely related to logic and computability theory, which are covered by the cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) sub-category. The paper also discusses the beta-reduction and complexity of deciding beta-eta equality, which are topics in programming languages and compilers, covered by the cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-category. The paper also mentions the game-semantic analysis of safety, which is related to the cs.TL (Temporal Logic) sub-category. The paper also discusses the representability of functions, which is related to the cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the characterization of the simply-typed lambda calculus, which is related to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category.
